addr="alex-nelson"
title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Consider <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-001Q.xml"
addr="nt-001Q"
title="Splitting field for x^{3}-2 over the rationals">the same polynomial as before but over a different field</fr:link>: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)=x^{3}-2]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{7}]]></fr:tex>. We see for any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c\in \mathbb {F}_{7}]]></fr:tex> that
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[c^{3}\equiv \pm 1\pmod {7},]]></fr:tex>
so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> has no root in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{7}]]></fr:tex>. Hence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> is irreducible.</fr:p><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk =\mathbb {F}_{7}[x]/(f(x))]]></fr:tex> which we write as <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{7}(\alpha )]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ^{3}=2]]></fr:tex>. We see <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\{2,4,1\}\subseteq \mathbb {F}_{7}^{\times }]]></fr:tex> are third roots of unity, so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(2\alpha )=f(4\alpha )=1]]></fr:tex>. Then
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[x^{3}-2=(x-\alpha )(x-2\alpha )(x-4\alpha )\in \Bbbk [x],]]></fr:tex>
so that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x^{3}-2]]></fr:tex> factors completely over an extension of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{7}]]></fr:tex> of degree 3.</fr:p>
 
   
